-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Fri Apr 11, 2014 09:30AM EDT
-- None



April 11 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1330 GMT on Friday:

** Patent buyer Intellectual Ventures has persuaded Microsoft Corp <MSFT.O> and Sony Corp <6758.T> to invest in its latest acquisition fund while Apple Inc <AAPL.O> and Intel Corp <INTC.O>, which invested with Intellectual Ventures previously, declined to participate, according to people briefed on the fundraising. [ID:nL2N0MZ163]  ** A buyout offer from India's billionaire Ruia family for Essar Energy Plc <ESSR.L> "materially undervalued" the company and its prospects, an independent committee set up to examine the offer said for a third time. [ID:nL3N0N33AP]  ** A small Australian exploration company said it had secured more than $6 billion in equity funding from unnamed investors to build a port and rail network to revive plans for a second iron ore export zone in the country. Padbury Mining <PDY.AX> said it was obtaining the funds from private Australian equity investors, who required anonymity, with an initial $470 million due in 40-45 days. [ID:nL3N0N3066]  ** Bank of Queensland Ltd <BOQ.AX> said it would buy the professional finance and leasing arm of South African-owned Investec's <INLJ.J> Australian unit for A$440 million ($414 million), aiming to boost credit quality and diversify outside its home state. [ID:nL3N0N30DM]  ** U.S. tax preparer H&R Block Inc <HRB.N> said on Thursday it would sell its bank unit to BofI Federal Bank, freeing the company from Federal Reserve oversight. [ID:nL3N0N24RI]  ** Petrolimex Bank, owned by Vietnam's top oil product importer and distributor Petrolimex, said it had received a takeover offer from VietinBank <CTG.HM>. [ID:nL3N0N311V]  ** Britain's Vodafone <VOD.L> said on Friday it had taken full ownership of Vodafone India by buying the 11 percent it did not already own from Piramal Enterprises Ltd <PIRA.NS>. [ID:nASM0006C6]  ** Austria's part-nationalized Volksbanken AG <OTVVp.VI> said on Friday that it had sold its Volksbank Malta unit to Mediterranean Bank <ANCPFM.UL>. Volksbanken did not give financial details. [ID:nWEB00LJ4]